-- #670 (S0 run‚Č†build memory fault): a range-slice `xs.[lo..hi]` (ESlice) carried
-- NO Slice/Index constraint, so `check` ACCEPTED it on ANY receiver -- even an
-- Int.  Native lowering routed it through the static "Array" type tag, so
-- `42.[0..1]` compiled to an `inttoptr`+`loadTag` of the immediate 42 and read the
-- never-mapped first page: `check` exit 0, `build`+exec SIGSEGV (exit 139), and a
-- polymorphic slice on a String silently leaked heap bytes at exit 0.
-- .expected = REJECT: `.[lo..hi]` now desugars to a `slice` Slice-method
-- call (#670), so a non-container receiver is unsatisfiable and check/run/build
-- must all reject BY DIAGNOSTIC (`No impl of Slice for Int`), never by crash.
f xs = xs.[0..1]
main = println (f 42)
